author: Google
description:
Where the Internet Lives is a Webby Award–winning podcast and mini-documentary series about the fascinating world of data centers. 

Join us as we venture into places few people ever see firsthand — and learn about the technology, people, and places that make the internet run. This film features Recursion, a groundbreaking clinical-stage TechBio company. Recursion is harnessing the power of data and AI to decode biology, dramatically improving the cost, timeline, and probability of success of developing new medicines for patients.

Want more? Check out seasons 3 and 4 of our series here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL590L5WQmH8dLLdbnJ775gPNvMeVWHLxT
Learn more about Google Data Centers here: https://datacenters.google/
